Macao experts warned residents to be careful but not panic over the bird flu that has killed children in neighboring Hong Kong.
They have increased inspections at Macao chicken farms and chicken markets, but nothing abnormal has been found.
The Department of Health prepared a fact sheet to explain to tourists the avian flu, which is caused by a virus H5N1 that is only found in poultry.
Eating chicken and other poultry would not pose a risk of H5N1 infection.
